state/
logs/
mailbox/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.superpowers/
supervisor/INCARNATION
supervisor/HANDSHAKE
# `_write_json_atomic` writes `<name>.tmp` beside its target before os.replace,
# and supervisor/ is git-tracked -- so every INCARNATION and HANDSHAKE write
# opens a window in which a runtime file with claim state in it is an untracked
# add. HANDSHAKE.tmp is not the lesser half: claim-nonce §6.4 puts
# `handoff_token_hash` and the successor's `nonce_hash` into HANDSHAKE.
# Glob, not two literals, so a third supervisor JSON store inherits the rule.
supervisor/*.tmp

# Scratch state from the `remember` tool: session-scoped notes plus a pid file.
# Arrived as an untracked add on `feat/worker-providers`; nothing in this repo reads it.
.remember/
